The paper deals with the problem of embedding the dual complex of rectangular partitions, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, such as the NP-completeness of the problem, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses sufficient conditions for a nice drawing, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
